<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="206" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,536,2039]" box="[151,266,536,562]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,266,536,562]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,536,562]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,536,2039]" box="[199,1099,572,599]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Mesosoma and metasoma dull orange; areolet petiolate; ovipositor sheath black.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,536,2039]" box="[199,659,608,635]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Female: fore wing length 
<quantity box="[488,654,608,635]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.3599999999999999" metricValueMin="1.04" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" unit="mm" value="12.0" valueMax="13.6" valueMin="10.4">10.4–13.6 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,536,2039]" box="[199,263,645,671]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,263,645,671]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Head</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,536,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Clypeus almost flat, with a weak transverse ridge near apex; malar space 0.6× as long as basal mandibular width (
<figureCitation box="[230,296,716,743]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[202,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. A. nigricornis (female specimen from Costa Rica), 5–8 Photographs, 9 Drawing. 5 Habitus (lateral view), 6 Habitus (dorsal view), 7 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), 8 Head (frontal view), 9 Fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810051/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); lower face at narrowest point 0.9× as wide as height from clypeofacial suture to insertion of antenna; hypostomal carina strongly raised, joined by occipital carina far from base of mandible; posterior ocellus separated the eye by 1.3–1.4× its own maximum diameter (
<figureCitation box="[708,777,788,815]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[202,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. A. nigricornis (female specimen from Costa Rica), 5–8 Photographs, 9 Drawing. 5 Habitus (lateral view), 6 Habitus (dorsal view), 7 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), 8 Head (frontal view), 9 Fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810051/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); antenna with first flagellomere about 1.0× as long as the second; subapical flagellomeres slightly elongated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,536,2039]" box="[199,325,861,887]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,861,887]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Mesosoma</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,536,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Pronotum with upper hind margin swollen, forming a small conical projection; scutoscutellar groove broad and shallow; scutellum shallow, with a few weak transverse rugae posteriorly; epicnemial carina more or less entirely absent (
<figureCitation box="[238,309,968,995]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[202,1386,181,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-21@2.[201,1386,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Lectotype of Apechoneura nigricornis Mocsary 1905 (female), 1–2 Photographs, 3–4 Drawings. 1 Habitus (lateral view), 2 Habitus (dorsal view), 3 Fore wing, 4 Hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810049/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[323,337,968,995]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[202,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. A. nigricornis (female specimen from Costa Rica), 5–8 Photographs, 9 Drawing. 5 Habitus (lateral view), 6 Habitus (dorsal view), 7 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), 8 Head (frontal view), 9 Fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810051/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">5</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[374,405,969,995]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[200,1388,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[199,1388,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–17. 10–13 A. nigricornis (female specimen from Colombia), 10, 11 &amp; 13 Photographs, 10 Habitus (lateral view), 11 Hind wing, 12 Hind wing (Drawing), 13 Apical part of metasoma. 14–17 A. nigricornis (male specimen from Costa Rica), 14, 15 &amp; 17 Photographs,14 Habitus (lateral view), 15 Habitus (dorsal view), 16 Hind wing (Drawing), 17 Head (frontal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810053" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810053/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">10</figureCitation>
); sternal region of mesothorax smooth and polished; posterior transverse carina represented only by small lateromedian crests (
<figureCitation box="[548,617,1004,1031]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[202,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. A. nigricornis (female specimen from Costa Rica), 5–8 Photographs, 9 Drawing. 5 Habitus (lateral view), 6 Habitus (dorsal view), 7 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), 8 Head (frontal view), 9 Fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810051/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); metapleuron with a conspicuous sharp lateral projection near posterior end (
<figureCitation box="[207,278,1040,1067]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[202,1386,181,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-21@2.[201,1386,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Lectotype of Apechoneura nigricornis Mocsary 1905 (female), 1–2 Photographs, 3–4 Drawings. 1 Habitus (lateral view), 2 Habitus (dorsal view), 3 Fore wing, 4 Hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810049/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Figs 1</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[314,330,1040,1067]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[202,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. A. nigricornis (female specimen from Costa Rica), 5–8 Photographs, 9 Drawing. 5 Habitus (lateral view), 6 Habitus (dorsal view), 7 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), 8 Head (frontal view), 9 Fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810051/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">5</figureCitation>
); submetapleural carina narrow with a distinct low median denticle; propodeum in profile more or less flat; anterior transverse carina mediodorsally incomplete so area basalis is not enclosed posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[1351,1421,1076,1103]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[202,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. A. nigricornis (female specimen from Costa Rica), 5–8 Photographs, 9 Drawing. 5 Habitus (lateral view), 6 Habitus (dorsal view), 7 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), 8 Head (frontal view), 9 Fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810051/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); area basalis slightly transverse; lateral longitudinal carina posteriorly weak or discontinuous (
<figureCitation box="[1199,1268,1112,1139]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[202,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. A. nigricornis (female specimen from Costa Rica), 5–8 Photographs, 9 Drawing. 5 Habitus (lateral view), 6 Habitus (dorsal view), 7 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), 8 Head (frontal view), 9 Fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810051/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); lateromedian longitudinal carinae joining anterior transverse carina at an angle of about 100 degrees, not present behind anterior transverse carina, even as a vestige (
<figureCitation box="[573,643,1184,1211]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[202,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. A. nigricornis (female specimen from Costa Rica), 5–8 Photographs, 9 Drawing. 5 Habitus (lateral view), 6 Habitus (dorsal view), 7 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), 8 Head (frontal view), 9 Fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810051/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); fore leg with tibia inflated, tarsus with long hairs on inner surface; mid leg with tibia bearing two or three stout spines on margin; hind coxa with anterior furrow deeply impressed, expanded ventrally, with a fringe of fine inconspicuous hairs; fore wing with areolet large, anteriorly pointed, with 2 
<emphasis box="[165,221,1293,1318]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">m-cu</emphasis>
joining it very slightly basal of middle (
<figureCitation box="[667,765,1292,1319]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[202,1386,181,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-21@2.[201,1386,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Lectotype of Apechoneura nigricornis Mocsary 1905 (female), 1–2 Photographs, 3–4 Drawings. 1 Habitus (lateral view), 2 Habitus (dorsal view), 3 Fore wing, 4 Hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810049/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[777,842,1292,1319]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[202,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. A. nigricornis (female specimen from Costa Rica), 5–8 Photographs, 9 Drawing. 5 Habitus (lateral view), 6 Habitus (dorsal view), 7 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), 8 Head (frontal view), 9 Fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810051/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">5 &amp; 9</figureCitation>
); second distal cell short, with vein 1 
<emphasis box="[1255,1311,1293,1318]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">m-cu</emphasis>
about 0.5× the length of abscissa of 
<emphasis box="[437,470,1329,1355]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Cu</emphasis>
1 between 
<emphasis box="[595,668,1329,1355]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Rs&amp;M</emphasis>
and 1 
<emphasis box="[739,795,1329,1354]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">m-cu</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[812,884,1328,1355]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[202,1386,181,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-21@2.[201,1386,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Lectotype of Apechoneura nigricornis Mocsary 1905 (female), 1–2 Photographs, 3–4 Drawings. 1 Habitus (lateral view), 2 Habitus (dorsal view), 3 Fore wing, 4 Hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810049/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Figs 3</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[923,939,1329,1355]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[202,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. A. nigricornis (female specimen from Costa Rica), 5–8 Photographs, 9 Drawing. 5 Habitus (lateral view), 6 Habitus (dorsal view), 7 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), 8 Head (frontal view), 9 Fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810051/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">9</figureCitation>
); hind wing with the distal abscissa of 
<emphasis box="[1390,1423,1329,1355]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Cu</emphasis>
1 joining 
<emphasis box="[238,288,1365,1390]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">cu-a</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[302,375,1364,1391]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[202,1386,181,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-21@2.[201,1386,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Lectotype of Apechoneura nigricornis Mocsary 1905 (female), 1–2 Photographs, 3–4 Drawings. 1 Habitus (lateral view), 2 Habitus (dorsal view), 3 Fore wing, 4 Hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810049/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Figs 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[387,481,1365,1391]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[200,1388,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[199,1388,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–17. 10–13 A. nigricornis (female specimen from Colombia), 10, 11 &amp; 13 Photographs, 10 Habitus (lateral view), 11 Hind wing, 12 Hind wing (Drawing), 13 Apical part of metasoma. 14–17 A. nigricornis (male specimen from Costa Rica), 14, 15 &amp; 17 Photographs,14 Habitus (lateral view), 15 Habitus (dorsal view), 16 Hind wing (Drawing), 17 Head (frontal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810053" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810053/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">11 &amp; 12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,536,2039]" box="[199,323,1401,1427]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,1401,1427]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Metasoma</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,536,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Tergite I slender, 3.8–3.9× as long as posteriorly broad; sternite I short, reaching about 0.3 of length of tergite, with a weak median swelling centrally; tergite II 1.9–2.0× as long as broad, with isolated pubescence; tergite VII mediodorsally without an indentation posteriorly; tergite VIII, in lateral view, tapered to a bluntly rounded apex, without a cornus, and with uniformly scattered pubescence; tergite IX bearing long pubescence; ovipositor at rest extending beyond apex of metasoma by 3.6–3.8× the length of the hind tibia.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,536,2039]" box="[199,267,1616,1642]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,1616,1642]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Color</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,536,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">A uniformly brownish orange species; flagellum black, with basal two flagellomeres ventrally reddish; tergite IX infuscate; ovipositor sheath uniformly blackish brown. Anterior two pairs of legs yellowish, hind leg orange with distal 0.7 of tibia and entire tarsus blackish. Fore wing hyaline, with a distinct subapical black spot; pterostigma black.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,536,2039]" box="[199,474,1796,1823]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1797,1823]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[275,402,1796,1823]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[200,1388,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[199,1388,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–17. 10–13 A. nigricornis (female specimen from Colombia), 10, 11 &amp; 13 Photographs, 10 Habitus (lateral view), 11 Hind wing, 12 Hind wing (Drawing), 13 Apical part of metasoma. 14–17 A. nigricornis (male specimen from Costa Rica), 14, 15 &amp; 17 Photographs,14 Habitus (lateral view), 15 Habitus (dorsal view), 16 Hind wing (Drawing), 17 Head (frontal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810053" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810053/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Figs 14–17</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[437,466,1797,1823]" captionStart="FIGURES 88–89" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1650,1674]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1626]" captionTargetId="figure-21@18.[151,1436,181,1626]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 88–89. 88 Distribution of A. nigricornis, 89 Distribution of A. nigriventris." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810085" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810085/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">88</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,536,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
Similar to female in structure, size and colour, hind coxa unspecialized; lower margin of tergite VII slightly turned under, bearing sparse long straight hairs that have their extreme ends turned about 90 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1175,1183,1868,1882]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">o</superScript>
; claspers with a fringe of scattered moderately long hairs; aedeagus compressed, obliquely truncate apically; subgenital plate bearing moderately close long pubescence.
</paragraph>
